itemDescription: English medical researcher and tuberculosis specialist

wikipedia_page.main: Professor John Grange (born 4 April 1943 at East Dereham, Norfolk) died 10 October 2016 was an English immunologist, epidemiologist, researcher, and academic, and was one of Europe's leading tuberculosis specialists.

response: *John Grange (immunologist) (born 1943), English physician, immunologist and epidemiologist
